					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-1227984">
																		Re: Small typo
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dreverettmann" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(323946); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=323946&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204458" alt="DrEverettMann" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=323946)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dreverettmann" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(323946); return false;" >DrEverettMann</a></span> <span class="odate time_1313178793 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Aug 2011 19:53</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1227984">
									

<p>Nope. To disappear and to be disappeared are very different things.</p>
<p>If her buddy had simply disappeared, there would be many different possible explanations. Maybe he'd run away. Maybe he'd had an accident and was dead in a ditch somewhere. Maybe he was kidnapped by aliens. Lots of possible things could happen to do that.</p>
<p>That he was disappeared carries somewhat different connotations. Being disappeared is what happens to political dissidents in dictatorships. It's what happens to witnesses to a politician's corruption. It's what the CIA allegedly does to inconvenient people.</p>
<p>See the difference?</p>

							</div>

								
					
